HEADWORD: lodgepole pine
<hw>lodgepole pine</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A tall, narrow 2-needled pine
(<spn>Pinus contorta</spn>) of the coastal Northwestern U. S., having a
red to yellow-brown bark fissured into small squares and bearing
egg-shaped cones.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> shore pine, lodgepole pine, spruce pine, <spn>Pinus
contorta</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

